The {popular labels} macro could use some more parameter, escpecially to limit results to a certain time frame to have a result list of popular labels for - let's say - the last 6 months or couple years.

If there's a space existing as long as Confluence will be used (by a company XY) there might be labelled content/pages which haven't been updated much often in the recent past and just might've been kept available for the sake of documentation. By having such content/pages heavily labelled anyway and - let's say - these labels are used much often as well (perhaps just in the past) - then we've such labels in our result list even though they are not important enough to appear in that list anymore.

Sometimes we rather have an overview of recently heavy used labels, especially as a service-oriented department in our company. I could imagine to have a parameter like {popular-labels:style=heatmap|count=15|timePeriod=Month|value=6}

Note: timePeriod=Month parameter is already available for the {chart} macro (Millisecond to Year), value could be added as well. Indeed we don't need values below days for the {popular labels} macro. :)


Same for the {recently-used-labels} macro which also does not allow to limit to a certain time frame.

Thanks in advance!

